noun.description: A native or inhabitant of Germany, or a person of German descent.
A West Germanic language used in Germany, Austria, and parts of Switzerland, and by communities in the US and elsewhere.
A complex dance in which one couple leads the other couples through a variety of figures and there is a continual change of partners.

origin: From Latin Germanus, used to designate related peoples of central and northern Europe, a name perhaps given by Celts to their neighbors; compare with Old Irish gair neighbor.
